HEADWORD: hediondilla
<hw>hediondilla</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A desert shrub (<spn>Larrea
tridentata</spn>) of the Southwestern U.S. and Northern Mexico having
persistent resinous aromatic foliage and small yellow flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> creosote bush, coville, <spn>Larrea
tridentata</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

